<title>FRANCE: Thomson-CSF to keep SGS-Thomson stake now.</title>
<headline>Thomson-CSF to keep SGS-Thomson stake now.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-04-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>French state-controlled defence electronics group Thomson-CSF said on Thursday that its board had decided, for the moment, not to exercise an option to sell its stake in components group SGS-Thomson.</p>
<p>The company announced its decision in a statement which noted that the option could be exercised up until September 30.</p>
<p>The decision concerns a of 17.4 percent stake in SGS Thomson, a spokesman added.</p>
